Post-Launch — V1.x Roadmap:
	V1.1 — Crash Reporting:
		- Create Sentry account and project (Scott) @tags(scott)
		- Integrate Sentry SDK via SPM
		- Implement opt-in crash reporting toggle in Settings (off by default)
		- Implement per-crash consent dialog for non-opted-in users ("SignalDrop quit unexpectedly. Send a crash report?")
		- Sentry SDK only initializes after user opts in — never before
		- Keep Sentry DSN out of public repo (environment variable or build setting)
	V1.x — Custom VPN Support:
		- Implement non-elevated custom VPN support (user provides name + CLI commands)
		- Custom VPN commands run at user-level permissions only (no privileged helper)
		- Settings UI for adding/editing/removing custom VPNs
	V1.x — VPN Library Expansion:
		- Add pre-configured CLI commands for popular VPNs: Mullvad, NordVPN, ExpressVPN, ProtonVPN, Surfshark, CyberGhost, OpenVPN, Cisco AnyConnect, GlobalProtect
	Future Improvements:
		- Move release pipeline to GitHub Actions CI
		- Landing page / marketing website (when domain is secured)
		- Consider user feedback platforms (Canny-style voting) if user base grows
		- Consider subreddit or community if user base grows
		- Setapp integration
		- App Store version (reduced feature set)

